OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 11 Mar to Fri 20 Mar
OL,6,FThe first part of this period will
OL,7,Fcontinue to see the UK located at the
OL,8,Finterface between high pressure across
OL,9,FEurope and low pressure over the North
OL,10,FAtlantic. As such, western areas will
OL,11,Flikely see spells of rain at times,
OL,12,Falong with stronger winds, whereas
OL,13,Feastern parts should see more in the
OL,14,Fway of drier interludes, though even
OL,15,Fhere, some rain is possible from time
OL,16,Fto time. Towards the middle of March,
OL,17,Fthere is a signal for unsettled
OL,18,Fconditions to perhaps become more
OL,19,Fwidespread, with all parts seeing a
OL,20,Fhigher chance of rain and stronger
OL,21,Fwinds. Throughout, temperatures should
OL,22,Foverall be a little above average for
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fmost areas.
